<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-01T15:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-17T16:00:00-05:00" n="672" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Moscow/10–1943</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">British Draft of Resolution on Peace Feelers From
                                Enemy Countries</hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-chapter-heading" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1943-11-01T23:59:59+03:00" notBefore="1943-10-18T00:00:00+03:00">undated</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">Conference Document No. 33</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“The Governments of the United Kingdom, the United States of America
                                and the U.S.S.R. agree to inform each other immediately of any
                                peace-feelers which they may receive from the Government of, or from
                                any groups or individuals in, a country with which any of them is at
                                war.</p>
                            <p>The three Governments further agree to consult together with a view
                                to concerting their action in regard to such approaches.”</p>
                        </quote>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>